    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Door Hinge</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Door Hinge</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Removal procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Hinge procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1603854" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603854.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Cab Door Hinge</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER HINGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER HINGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HINGE BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CAB HINGE PILLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LOCKING BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The cab door is mounted on upper and lower hinges located on the cab hinge pillar. Door
                        adjustment is provided by enlarged holes in the door hinge mounting holes. If door hinges are
                        removed from the cab, upper and lower hinges can be interchanged.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cab door from the hinges. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603811.xml" xrefid="x1603811">
                        <emph type="bold">CAB DOORS</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603811"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark upper and lower hinge positions on cab hinge pillar to simplify door adjustment
                    during installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark the location of the locking bolt, so it can be installed in the correct location.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hinge bolt, locking bolt, and upper hinge from cab hinge pillar.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two hinge bolts and lower hinge from cab hinge pillar.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Installation procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Hinge procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align lower hinge with previously made marks on cab hinge pillar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603854">Figure 73, Items 2 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install lower hinge and secure with two hinge bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603854">Figure 73, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts to 15 to 18 Lbf-ft (20
                    to 24 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align upper hinge with previously made marks on cab hinge pillar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603854">Figure 73, Items 1 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install upper hinge and secure with hinge bolt and locking bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603854">Figure 73, Items 1, 3, and 5</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts to 15 to 18 Lbf-ft
                    (20 to 24 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the cab door on the hinges. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603811.xml" xrefid="x1603811">
                        <emph type="bold">CAB DOORS</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603811"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
